Package: PIPoL
Type: Package
Title: Propensity-weighted Influence Propagation of Labels in Host-Microbiome Interactive Network
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Zixu",
           family = "Hao",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "your_email@georgetown.edu")
Description: 
    Implements PIPoL (Robust Inference via Phylogeny-aware Label Propagation),
    a tree-aware framework for identifying core, intermediate, and transient
    taxa in microbiome studies. The method jointly models abundance-based
    co-enrichment and prevalence-based co-existence using host-taxon bipartite
    graphs and phylogenetic kernel smoothing. PIPoL supports inverse probability
    weighting to adjust for confounding and provides principled decontamination
    via joint significance in weighted and unweighted propagation spaces.
